originalText.text: I've seen much better..I've seen much worse. It serves its purpose. The woman in management office  who takes care of my rent is very nice she has always been for the last four years my son and I have lived  here. Miss.M. there is a (semi new) building manager- Miss R. That is very friendly ..compared to the old one anyone would seem friendly but she actually is very pleasant to be around. I find it funny that a woman writes all this horrible stuff about living here for four years of hell....if I was in hell... I'd have moved 2 years and 11 months ago. Her review sounds silly. I happen to be on a very quiet ,clean floor, the neighbors are older not 19 20 year olds that blast music all night. I feel like if your floor is good the rest is up to u....keep your house nice and cozy and your family well....and you will live well... if you look for reasons to complain...you will find them no matter what area or area or buildin you live in. Such is life ... I hope this is mow 200 character bc I'm not sure how the points work..but I'm tryma get them up there quick but doin these  irrelevant ro me...but def important to inform others type of reviews.

originalText.text: This is the worst development I have ever encountered in my life. The management office is a joke. I lived there for 4 years and had nothing but problems that never get resolve. They were so horrible that one of the rachett staff got in my face and told me she wanted to go and i wasn't the only one trying to go home to a family. Mind you they close at 430 but apparently they lock the doors at 415. Clearly you don't need degree maybe not even a diploma to work at this place. My housing manager would hang up on me, be disrespectful and lie to say she wasnt there when I could clearly see her in the office clear as a day. Needs to hire people that actual care about their job. DO NOT RECOMMEND EVER LIVING HEREEEE !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
